Note:
P1-B smoke test: verify file_metadata.runa now performs real stat
syscalls instead of returning uninitialized garbage from the broken
syscall2 thunk.

The test exits with a Process return code that encodes which case
failed. 200 means all checks passed. Other codes are stable per-case
diagnostics:

    100 file_exists("/etc/passwd") was not 1 (existing path)
    101 file_exists("/nonexistent_xyz_abc") was not 0 (HARD CUTOVER)
    102 get_file_size("/etc/passwd") was not greater than 0
    103 is_directory("/tmp") was not 1
    104 is_directory("/etc/passwd") was not 0
    200 ALL PASS

Hard-cutover check (101) is the critical regression gate: pre-P1-B
the broken thunk caused do_stat to always succeed with garbage, so
file_exists always returned 1 even for nonexistent paths. Post-P1-B
the real stat syscall returns -ENOENT for missing paths and
file_exists correctly returns 0.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/io/file_metadata.runa" as FileMetadata

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Note: ------------------------------------------------------------
    Note: Case 1: existing path /etc/passwd must report exists.
    Note: ------------------------------------------------------------
    Let exists_real be proc file_exists from FileMetadata with "/etc/passwd"
    If exists_real is not equal to 1:
        Return 100
    End If

    Note: ------------------------------------------------------------
    Note: Case 2: nonexistent path must report 0 (HARD CUTOVER behavior).
    Note: Pre-P1-B this returned 1 because the broken syscall2 thunk
    Note: always returned 0 which do_stat treated as success.
    Note: ------------------------------------------------------------
    Let exists_fake be proc file_exists from FileMetadata with "/nonexistent_xyz_abc_p1b_check"
    If exists_fake is not equal to 0:
        Return 101
    End If

    Note: ------------------------------------------------------------
    Note: Case 3: get_file_size must read a plausible size from the
    Note: real stat buffer. /etc/passwd is normally hundreds of bytes;
    Note: we conservatively require > 0 because exact size varies per
    Note: host. Pre-P1-B this read uninitialized arena memory.
    Note: ------------------------------------------------------------
    Let passwd_size be proc get_file_size from FileMetadata with "/etc/passwd"
    If passwd_size is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 102
    End If

    Note: ------------------------------------------------------------
    Note: Case 4: is_directory("/tmp") must report 1. This exercises
    Note: get_file_permissions -> get_file_type -> bitmask extraction
    Note: on a directory. Pre-P1-B all three operated on garbage.
    Note: ------------------------------------------------------------
    Let tmp_is_dir be proc is_directory from FileMetadata with "/tmp"
    If tmp_is_dir is not equal to 1:
        Return 103
    End If

    Note: ------------------------------------------------------------
    Note: Case 5: is_directory on a regular file must report 0. Catches
    Note: the case where get_file_type returns wrong upper-4-bit mask.
    Note: ------------------------------------------------------------
    Let passwd_is_dir be proc is_directory from FileMetadata with "/etc/passwd"
    If passwd_is_dir is not equal to 0:
        Return 104
    End If

    Return 200
End Process
